Overview of CTGAN
• Generator uses Batch-normalization and ReLU activation
function [2].
• Synthetic row representation is generated using mixed
activation functions[2].
• Scalar values are generated by Tanh[2].
• Mode indicator and discrete values are generated by Gumbel
Softmax[2].
• Discriminator uses Leaky ReLU function and dropout on each
hidden layer[2].

Taiwanese Bankruptcy Prediction Data Set
• Number of Instances: 6819
• Number of Attributes: 96


/
CTGAN Model Training
• Batch Size= 500
• Epochs= 10000
• Embedding Dimension= 128
• Generator Dimension= (256, 256)
• Discriminator Dimension= (256, 256)
• Generator Learning Rate = 0.001
• Discriminator Learning Rate = 0.001
• Taken from Benchmark implementation [2]
